1 unit Cucumber
4 ounce Grape Tomatoes
¼ ounce Dill
1 unit Lemon
2 unit Pita Bread
½ ounce Pepitas
3 tablespoon Sour Cream
½ cup Hummus
1 cup Feta Cheese
2 teaspoon Hot Sauce
Salt
Pepper
2 teaspoon Olive Oil
4 ounce Roasted Red Pepper Spread

• Wash and dry produce.

• Quarter cucumber lengthwise; slice into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve
tomatoes. Pick and roughly chop fronds from dill. Halve lemon.
Halve pitas.

• In a medium bowl, toss together cucumber, tomatoes, pepitas, half the
dill, a large drizzle of olive oil, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.
Season generously with salt and pepper.

• In a small bowl, combine sour cream, remaining dill, and a squeeze of
lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

• Wrap pitas in damp paper towels and place on a plate. Microwave until
warm, 20 seconds. Fill pitas with a bit of hummus, half the roasted red
pepper spread (all for 4 servings), veggie salad, dill sauce, feta, and hot
sauce to taste. Serve.